    <div class="markdown">
        <h1>Project topic : Global Cybersecurity Threats (2015–2024)</h1>
    </div>
    <div class="markdown">
        <strong>Problem Statement:</strong><br>
        Cybersecurity incidents have been increasing rapidly, causing huge financial losses and impacting millions of users worldwide. Analyzing patterns in cybersecurity attacks can help identify vulnerabilities and mitigate future threats.
        <br><br>
        <strong>Objectives:</strong>
        <ol>
            <li>To analyze cybersecurity threat data from 2015 to 2024.</li>
            <li>To identify trends in attacks, affected industries, and financial losses.</li>
            <li>To visualize relationships between users affected, losses, and attack types.</li>
            <li>To compare different attack sources and resolution mechanisms.</li>
        </ol>
    </div>
    <div class="markdown">
        <strong>Scope of the Project:</strong><br>
        This project focuses on exploring cybersecurity threats using data visualization and analysis techniques. Provides insights that can guide future security strategies.
    </div>
    <div class="markdown">
        <strong>Programming Languages:</strong><br>
        Python (for data analysis and visualization)<br>
        <strong>Libraries/Frameworks:</strong><br>
        Pandas → data loading, cleaning, preprocessing<br>
        NumPy → numerical operations<br>
        Matplotlib → visualizations (plots, charts)<br>
        Seaborn → advanced statistical plots
    </div>

